column5: Been pretty frosty up here with wind chills in the -50's for the last week. Made it back alive!!! Pic from the trip.  ?
Taken at high noon no doubt.
Jesus. How does anyone survive up there? Is that a dog sled behind you?
There comes a moment when you have to make a choice,  I think I'd be going to the store, I mean you have to go there to get the rest of the groceries anyway.

An old family photo of his great great great grandfather. This man owns a villa on a lake with all of the toys. The sled gave it away. he is sitting in hot room having a beer! try  pulling our leg big time. Right Dave?

The fish would be flash frozen before you take the hook out. If that is you Big Dave, you nuts mon, berry berry nuts. I was in Florida for a few days last month, it was 55F in Naples and people said they were freezing and all the wealthy ladies were wearing their furs.

NAH, not me. Just some Inuit guy up on the sea ice. I'm too old fer that shizzz!!!  ? Finally got out to the cabin for the first time since October today though. Man the snow in the bush on my trail is deep this year. Had a heck of a time breaking trail with my 10 foot long 700# touring sled.  ?
You need some oil drilling equipment to get thru the ice up there.
